<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="167">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="167">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="167">Thorax</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Pronotum with three pairs of rounded tubercles: SMs, SLs, and Ls. Mesonotum with three pairs of tubercles: two pairs of SMMs and LAs (lateral anterior tubercles), and an unpaired MP tubercle (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 12. Larva of Teloganodes barathyae Sivaruban, Martynov, Srinivasan &amp; Isack, sp. nov., paratypes A total view, dorsal view B total view, ventral view C head and thorax, dorsal view D pronotum, dorso-lateral view E head, dorsal view F abdomen, ventral view. Abbreviations: white arrows show tubercles." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1113.85448.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/716510" pageId="0" pageNumber="167">12C, D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="167">
Forefemur (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Larva of Teloganodes barathyae Sivaruban, Martynov, Srinivasan &amp; Isack, sp. nov., paratypes A fore femur B middle femur C hind femur D outer margin of hind femur E fore tibia F, G tarsal claw, ventral F and lateral G view. Abbreviations: black arrows show subapical denticles and setae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1113.85448.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/716512" pageId="0" pageNumber="167">14A</figureCitation>
) moderately broad, ca 2.4 times longer than wide; outer margin with a regular row of long, stout, hair-like setae. Dorsal surface with submarginal row of numerous short, stout setae with divergent margins (some of setae divided near apex into two rounded lobes); same stout setae scattered over whole dorsal surface; inner margin with a regular row of long, stout hair-like setae, this row continuing on dorsal surface to near articulation with trochanter; transverse row of stout setae absent. Dorsal surface of fore tibia with oblique regular row of long, stout, hair-like setae and solitary hair-like setae; outer margins of tibia with a regular row of long, stout, hair-like setae (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Larva of Teloganodes barathyae Sivaruban, Martynov, Srinivasan &amp; Isack, sp. nov., paratypes A fore femur B middle femur C hind femur D outer margin of hind femur E fore tibia F, G tarsal claw, ventral F and lateral G view. Abbreviations: black arrows show subapical denticles and setae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1113.85448.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/716512" pageId="0" pageNumber="167">14E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption doi="10.3897/zookeys.1113.85448.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/716512" pageId="0" pageNumber="167" start="Figure 14" startId="F14">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="167">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="167">Figure 14.</emphasis>
Larva of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sivaruban, Martynov, Srinivasan &amp; Isack" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Teloganodidae" genus="Teloganodes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Teloganodes barathyae" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="167" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barathyae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="167">Teloganodes barathyae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Sivaruban, Martynov, Srinivasan &amp; Isack, sp. nov., paratypes 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="167">A</emphasis>
fore femur 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="167">B</emphasis>
middle femur 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="167">C</emphasis>
hind femur 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="167">D</emphasis>
outer margin of hind femur 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="167">E</emphasis>
fore tibia 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="167">F, G</emphasis>
tarsal claw, ventral 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="167">F</emphasis>
and lateral 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="167">G</emphasis>
view. Abbreviations: black arrows show subapical denticles and setae.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="167">
Middle and hind femora with ornamentation similar to foreleg (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Larva of Teloganodes barathyae Sivaruban, Martynov, Srinivasan &amp; Isack, sp. nov., paratypes A fore femur B middle femur C hind femur D outer margin of hind femur E fore tibia F, G tarsal claw, ventral F and lateral G view. Abbreviations: black arrows show subapical denticles and setae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1113.85448.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/716512" pageId="0" pageNumber="167">14B-D</figureCitation>
). Middle and hind tibiae with a row of long and stout, hair-like setae on outer margin; dorsal surface with oblique row of long, stout, hair-like setae; also scattered short, stout setae with divergent margins (some of the setae divided near apex into two rounded lobes) present on dorsal surface along outer margin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="167">
Tarsal claw hooked, bearing four medial denticles and two subapical denticles on opposite sides of claw; dorsal and ventral surface of claw with a row of 3-5 subapical, hair-like setae (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Larva of Teloganodes barathyae Sivaruban, Martynov, Srinivasan &amp; Isack, sp. nov., paratypes A fore femur B middle femur C hind femur D outer margin of hind femur E fore tibia F, G tarsal claw, ventral F and lateral G view. Abbreviations: black arrows show subapical denticles and setae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1113.85448.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/716512" pageId="0" pageNumber="167">14F, G</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="167">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="167">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="167">Abdomen</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Median tubercles on terga I-X present; on tergum I poorly developed; on terga II-IV moderately developed; on terga V-X most developed. In dorsal view tubercles I-IX broad and rounded apically, tubercle X distinctly slender and bluntly pointed (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="F15" captionText="Figure 15. Larva of Teloganodes barathyae Sivaruban, Martynov, Srinivasan &amp; Isack, sp. nov., paratypes A abdomen, dorsal view B abdomen, lateral view C median tubercle of abdominal tergum VI D gill V E gill VI F setae of caudal filament." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1113.85448.figure15" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/716513" pageId="0" pageNumber="167">15A, B</figureCitation>
). Median tubercles with short, stout setae (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="F15" captionText="Figure 15. Larva of Teloganodes barathyae Sivaruban, Martynov, Srinivasan &amp; Isack, sp. nov., paratypes A abdomen, dorsal view B abdomen, lateral view C median tubercle of abdominal tergum VI D gill V E gill VI F setae of caudal filament." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1113.85448.figure15" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/716513" pageId="0" pageNumber="167">15C</figureCitation>
). Posterolateral projections present on segments II-IX; slightly marked on segments I-VI; most distinct on segments VII-IX (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 12. Larva of Teloganodes barathyae Sivaruban, Martynov, Srinivasan &amp; Isack, sp. nov., paratypes A total view, dorsal view B total view, ventral view C head and thorax, dorsal view D pronotum, dorso-lateral view E head, dorsal view F abdomen, ventral view. Abbreviations: white arrows show tubercles." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1113.85448.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/716510" pageId="0" pageNumber="167">12F</figureCitation>
). Submedian and sublateral areas of terga VI and VII with differently sized (mainly medium-length and long) stout setae with slightly or moderately divided apices.
</paragraph>
<caption doi="10.3897/zookeys.1113.85448.figure15" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/716513" pageId="0" pageNumber="167" start="Figure 15" startId="F15">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="167">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="167">Figure 15.</emphasis>
Larva of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sivaruban, Martynov, Srinivasan &amp; Isack" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Teloganodidae" genus="Teloganodes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Teloganodes barathyae" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="167" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barathyae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="167">Teloganodes barathyae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Sivaruban, Martynov, Srinivasan &amp; Isack, sp. nov., paratypes 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="167">A</emphasis>
abdomen, dorsal view 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="167">B</emphasis>
abdomen, lateral view 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="167">C</emphasis>
median tubercle of abdominal tergum VI 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="167">D</emphasis>
gill V 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="167">E</emphasis>
gill VI 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="167">F</emphasis>
setae of caudal filament.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="167">
Gills present on abdominal segments II-VI. Gill II with dorsal lamella operculate and covering others, oval with margin entire; gills II-V with well-developed flabelliform ventral lobe; gills III-V with dorsal lamella incised medially (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="F15" captionText="Figure 15. Larva of Teloganodes barathyae Sivaruban, Martynov, Srinivasan &amp; Isack, sp. nov., paratypes A abdomen, dorsal view B abdomen, lateral view C median tubercle of abdominal tergum VI D gill V E gill VI F setae of caudal filament." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1113.85448.figure15" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/716513" pageId="0" pageNumber="167">15D</figureCitation>
); gill VI with dorsal lamella entire (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="F15" captionText="Figure 15. Larva of Teloganodes barathyae Sivaruban, Martynov, Srinivasan &amp; Isack, sp. nov., paratypes A abdomen, dorsal view B abdomen, lateral view C median tubercle of abdominal tergum VI D gill V E gill VI F setae of caudal filament." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1113.85448.figure15" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/716513" pageId="0" pageNumber="167">15E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="167">
Central portion of cerci with elongate stout setae with bluntly pointed apices and few long, hair-like setae; stout setae length less than half length of the corresponding segment (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="F15" captionText="Figure 15. Larva of Teloganodes barathyae Sivaruban, Martynov, Srinivasan &amp; Isack, sp. nov., paratypes A abdomen, dorsal view B abdomen, lateral view C median tubercle of abdominal tergum VI D gill V E gill VI F setae of caudal filament." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1113.85448.figure15" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/716513" pageId="0" pageNumber="167">15F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="167">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="167">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="167">Winged stages</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
